scenes.title: ball
scenes.content: The Zome ball has 62 holes in icosahedral symmetry.  Thirty rectangles are for blue struts, twenty triangles are for yellow struts, and twelve pentagons are for red struts.

scenes.title: blue
scenes.content: The blue lines define fifteen mirrors, which form a spherical kaleidoscope that gives us the icosahedral reflection group.  Each mirror is orthogonal to a single blue line, and corresponds to two opposite rectangles on the face of the ball.

scenes.title: red
scenes.content: The red lines form at the intersection of five mirror planes, and therefore give us fivefold rotational symmetry.  This is why red struts have a pentagonal cross-section.

scenes.title: yellow
scenes.content: The yellow lines form at the intersection of three mirror planes, and therefore give us threefold rotational symmetry.  This is why yellow struts have a triangular cross-section.

scenes.title: frame
scenes.content: Every blue line forms an orthogonal frame with two other blue lines.  There are five frames in total.  This means you can build a compound of five cubes, even though there is no true cubic symmetry in the system.

scenes.title: dodecahedron
scenes.content:
Zome inherently supports building a pentagon, and a dodecahedron, using blue lines.

The center of a dodecahedron is what defines the length of yellow struts relative to blue struts.

Every ball in a connected Zome structure has the same orientation.  Valid structures do not require any bending or twisting.

scenes.title: dualize
scenes.content: We can replace every dodecahedron edge with an orthogonal blue strut at one scale larger.

scenes.title: duals
scenes.content: Doing this everywhere gives us an icosahedron, the dual of the dodecahedron.

scenes.title: icosahedron
scenes.content: The center of an icosahedron is what defines the length of red struts relative to blue struts.

scenes.title: blue lengths
scenes.content: Zometool struts come in three sizes, with scaling between them by the golden ratio.

scenes.title: long blues
scenes.content: Older Zometool sets were one scale larger overall, including B3 struts but no B0 struts.

scenes.title: red lengths
scenes.content: Red struts also come in three sizes, with golden ratio scaling.

scenes.title: long reds
scenes.content: Older Zometool sets included R3 struts but no R0 struts.

scenes.title: yellow lengths
scenes.content: Yellow struts also come in three sizes, with golden ratio scaling.

scenes.title: long yellows
scenes.content: Older Zometool sets included Y3 struts but no Y0 struts.
